---
title: "RxCheck : Resetting your Mobile Authenticator App"
parent: "RxConsole User Guide"
nav_order: 54
---
1. Users can set up or reset their authenticator app by:

a. Scanning the QR code from their RxConsole account creation email, or

b. Clicking *Reset QR Code* on the authenticator code screen

1. If you clicked the *Reset QR Code* link, press the *Email QR Code* button on the following screen.
2. A *Reset QR Code – Email Sent* pop-up will display. Press the *Ok* button.

3. Users will receive an email from “prod-notif” with the subject **Reset QR Code**.

4. Open the email and scan the QR Code.

*The QR code here is for reference only.*

![image-20251218-154848.png](attachments/178388994/179568641.png?width=207)![image-20251218-154948.png](attachments/178388994/179339281.png?width=234)![image-20251218-155003.png](attachments/178388994/178389001.png?width=246)![image-20251218-155039.png](attachments/178388994/178323459.png?width=200)![image-20251218-155125.png](attachments/178388994/179077123.png?width=84)

If the user previously set up authentication in a mobile authenticator app, they should delete the existing RxConsole account entry in that authenticator app before scanning the new QR code to avoid duplicate entries.